    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six M96 engine paired with a 6-speed manual transaxle. This example is mechanically sound, benefiting from a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced Rear Main Seal (RMS). The suspension architecture remains sharp, utilizing McPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup for exceptional lateral grip and communicative feedback. The power delivery is linear, peaking at 320hp with a visceral exhaust note. The chassis is rigid, and the braking system retains its firm pedal feel with cross-drilled rotors. This is a driver-focused machine with a well-maintained drivetrain, ready for high-revving engagement.",
